        <a name='S6CV0352P0_20000621_WH_99'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-elfyn-llwyd' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0352P0_20000621_WH_99' title='Link to this speech by Mr Elfyn Llwyd' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-elfyn-llwyd" title="Mr Elfyn Llwyd">Mr. Llwyd</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Did the hon. Lady hear me earlier refer to the fact that the Government departed from that general rule in no fewer than three instances in the latest Budget statement? Furthermore, did she not listen when I said that the Minister for Local Government and the Regions has already given cast-iron assurances via the Treasury to the three English regions now getting objective 1 status?
